Q1.Create a file and add executable permission to all users (user, group and others)

touch file1.sh
anish@ANISHKUMAR:~$ ls -l file1.sh
-rw-r--r-- 1 anish anish 0 Feb 12 09:01 file1.sh
anish@ANISHKUMAR:~$ chmod +x file1.sh
anish@ANISHKUMAR:~$ ls -l file1.sh
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q2. Create a file and remove write permission for group user alone

touch file2.txt
chmod g-w file2.txt
ls -l file2.txt
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q3. Create a file and add a soft link in a different directory

mkdir dir1 dir2
touch dir2/file3.txt
ln -s ../dir2/file3.txt dir1/file3_link.txt
ls -l dir1
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q4. Use ps command with options to display all active processes

ps -ef
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q5. Create three files in a directory and redirect the sorted list output to a file

cd dir1
touch a.txt b.txt c.txt
ls -lt > output.txt
cat output.txt
